<subpara id="RM000000ZUQ008X_03" type-id="51" category="05" proc-id="RM0250U___00005GY00001">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten3>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>When replacing the tire pressure warning ECU, read the IDs stored in the ECU using the intelligent tester and write them down before removal.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>It is necessary to perform initialization (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000XMZ008X"/>) after registration (See page <xref label="Seep02" href="RM000000XN1008X"/>) of the transmitter IDs into the tire pressure warning ECU after the ECU and/or valve and transmitter has been replaced.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten3>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Set the tire pressure to the specified value.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000ZUQ008X_05" type-id="01" category="01">
<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM000000ZUQ008X_05_0047" proc-id="RM0250U___00005H700001">
<testtitle>CHECK FREQUENCY RECEIVING CONDITION</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Check if the vehicle is not located in areas such as described below:</ptxt>
<test2>
<ptxt>Facilities or devices that use similar radio frequencies are located in the vicinity of the vehicle.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>If the vehicle is located in areas described above, the tire pressure warning light may come on only in a particular area.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</test2>
<test2>
<ptxt>Devices using similar radio frequencies are used in the vehicle.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>Facilities, or devices that use similar radio frequencies are not located in the vicinity of the vehicle.</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Radio frequency may be interrupted due to surroundings or devices installed by user.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</test2>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000ZUQ008X_05_0034" fin="false">OK</down>
<right ref="RM000000ZUQ008X_05_0055" fin="true">NG</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
